{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2024-01-05","name":"Emma Cauz","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Emma Cauz","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Emma"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"Cauz"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Emma De Caux","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1208–1251","fullLifespan":"1208–before 1251","portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/ciq1j/thumb200s.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7760-122900-12726-47/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/163607608","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7760-122900-12726-47/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7760-122900-12726-47/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"}],"birthDate":"+1208","birthPlace":{"address":"Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England","geo":{"latitude":51.35394,"longitude":-1.562,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathPlace":{"address":"England","geo":{"latitude":52.4379,"longitude":-1.6496,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\n1208 Birth and Parents\nEmma de Cauz was the daughter and heiress of Roger de Cauz \n\nFather Roger de Cauz\n\nMother Nichole de Leigh\n\nEmma de Cauz was born at Shalbourne, Buckinghamshire, Shalbourne & Eaton Grey, Wiltshire, England.\n\nBirth Year Estimation\n\nHer first husband died in 1230 and there were no children. Assume this was a short marriage, contracted in, say, 1225, at which time John de Segrave was 25 and Emma aged 20, thus born, say, 1205 or 1208\n\n«b»First Marriage to John de Segrave«/b»\nShe married John de Segrave, who died s. p. 1230, son of Sir Stephen de Segrave, Lord Segrave, Sheriff of Buckinghamshire, Bedfordshire, Worcestershire, Leicestershire, & Northamptonshire, Justiciar of England and Rohese Despenser.\n\n«b»Second Marriage to John de Grey«/b»\nEmma de Cauz married Sir John de Grey, Sheriff of Buckingham & Bedford, who died shortly before 19 March 1265/6, son of Henry de Grey, 1st Baron Grey of Codnor and Isolda de Bardolf, circa 1234.\n\n«b»Issue«/b»\n1.) Nichole de Grey d. a 30 May 1277\n\n2.) Sir Reginald de Grey, 1st Lord Grey of Wilton+ d. 5 Apr 1308\n\n3.) Emme de Grey b. c 1235, d. 1264","sourceList":[{"title":"Emma de Cauz - Medlands - FMG","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/enguntac.htm#EmmaCauzMJohnSegrave","sourceUri":"QKYS-S8D"},{"title":"The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints, International Genealogical index","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceUri":"QVCB-S7D"},{"title":"Emma de Cauz - Medlands - FMG","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/ENGLISHNOBILITYMEDIEVAL3D-K.htm#_Toc64628875","sourceUri":"3RWP-4S2"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1208","date":"1208","place":"Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1219","date":"1219","place":"Shirland, Derbyshire, England","age":"11","id":"LZG9-8W4"},{"name":"Death of Spouse","sources":"0","year":"1231","date":"1231","age":"23","id":"GKGJ-FVZ"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"1232","date":"about 1232","place":"London, England","type":"Spousal","age":"24","id":"MHCC-ZNJ"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1240","date":"1240","place":"Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England","age":"32","id":"9CJC-ZH9"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1240","date":"1 April 1240","place":"Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England","age":"32","id":"K2JK-6TY"},{"name":"Death","sources":"1","year":"1251","date":"before 1251","place":"England","age":"42"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"1207","date":"1207","place":"Shirland, Derbyshire, England","type":"Parent