re, England":"Shirland, Derbyshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cauz","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Jewish (Ashkenazic): variant of   Katz  .","Americanized form of German   Katz  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Katz","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Hyman, Isadore, Meyer, Moshe, Chaim, Emanuel, Aron, Mayer, Shoshana, Zev.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): acronymic surname from the first letters of the Hebrew phrase <i>kohen tsedek</i> ‘priest of righteousness’ (see   Cohen  ).","German: nickname from <i>Katz(e)</i> ‘cat’. See also English   Catt  , compare   Catz   and   Kates  ."]}]},{"name":"Emma","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Old French name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, originally a short form of compound names such as   Ermintrude   containing the word <i>erm(en)</i>, <i>irm(en)</i> ‘entire’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, but its popularity in medieval England was greatly enhanced by the fact that it had been borne by the mother of Edward the Confessor, herself a Norman. In modern times, it was only in moderate use early in the 20th century but rose sharply in favour in the 1970s and has since remained perennially popular."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":7,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":16,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Emma Cauz was born in 1208, in Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England, her father, Roger de Cauz, was 30 and her mother, Nicole Leigh, was 23. She married John De Grey Sheriff of Nottingham and Derby about 1232, in London, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died before 1251, in England."},"et":{"1208–before 1251":"1208–enne 1251","1208–1251":"1208–1251","1205–1266":"1205–1266","1200–1231":"1200–1231","1240–1308":"1240–1308","1178–1219":"1178–1219","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1 April 1240":"1. aprill 1240","1231":"1231","1240":"1240","1185":"1185","1251":"1251","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1178":"1178","1200":"1200","1266":"1266","before 1251":"enne 1251","about 1232":"umbes 1232","1308":"1308","1208":"1208","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England":"Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England","Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","London, England":"London, England","Shirland, Derbyshire, England":"Shirland, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"1208–before 1251":"1208–ennen vuotta 1251","1208–1251":"1208–1251","1205–1266":"1205–1266","1200–1231":"1200–1231","1240–1308":"1240–1308","1178–1219":"1178–1219","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1 April 1240":"1. huhtikuuta 1240","1231":"1231","1240":"1240","1185":"1185","1251":"1251","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1178":"1178","1200":"1200","1266":"1266","before 1251":"ennen vuotta 1251","about 1232":"noin 1232","1308":"1308","1208":"1208","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England":"Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England","Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","London, England":"London, England","Shirland, Derbyshire, Englan